{
  "stem": "11179.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we got well fed and a lot of us worked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The younger people worked for the armed forces and we got paid-- when I was working for the army, we got paid in American money.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we still stayed in camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We still weren't affluent, but we-- life had changed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was much better, but we didn't want to stay there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so far, we saw no opening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Palestine was still basically closed, as you-- as you remember, probably, or know-- was still basically closed for Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mainly, Harry Truman did sign into law, and I think Senator Jacob Jeffers and Congressman Emanuel Celler-- I don't know if you remember those names-- helped with that, that they would use a quota, yes.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, there was a quota for immigrants.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "An affidavit without a quota, your number was no good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to wait.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The German quota was approximately 14,000 a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Quota was based on 1920-- the-- the geographical condition in 1920.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Many Jews who were-- German Jews-- lived in-- Poland was-- did not-- that was one of the times when Poland was occupied part by Germany, part by Austria, and part by Russia.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So after World War I, Poland was existing again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the Jews who lived there remembered the pogroms.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They didn't want any part of Russia, they didn't want any part of Poland, and they figured they prefer to stay in Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were German speaking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was a province of Posen in West Prussia, and in Austria, Galicia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, those people went to-- most of them went to Australia or Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the American quota system was such that they fell under Polish quota because it was 1920 Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
